Johannesburg - Police are investigating after R24 million in cash was stolen from a plane at OR Tambo International Airport on Tuesday evening. People in a marked police car intercepted the money from an SAA flight which had just landed, sources said. - Read more: R24m 'police car' heist at OR Tambo airportHawks spokesperson Brigadier Hangwani Mulaudzi said a high-level investigation, involving all law enforcement agencies, was underway. Flights were unaffected.South Africans took to social media to react to the news of the dramatic heist. See some of the tweets here.&nbsp;Who knew what and when? There is no way this was not an inside job. The police must just concentrate their efforts on OR Tambo security ppl.&mdash; Amukelani (@amufloyd) March 8, 2017@SakinaKamwendo Why r we surprised abt heist @ OR Tambo? bcs McBride mentioned these shenanigans in Parliament not so long ago&mdash; Sbojero (@CweniSibonile) March 8, 2017@SakinaKamwendo what happened at OR Tambo last night shows the cracks in our security system. Wonder how many drugs goes unnoticed there?&mdash; Mosh432 (@makakasemm) March 8, 2017They just stole 24 Million from OR Tambo. Definitely an inside job. How can you rob a whole international airport? Italian job of note ??&mdash; Sicelo (@SiceloDumakude) March 7, 2017OR Tambo heist just left me speechless. Shiiiit! We are in trouble! #ORTamboHeist #ORTamboRobbery&mdash; Sikhosonke (@psyckhosonkevic) March 8, 2017How many are going to die for this money as what happened with the previous 11mil heist also at OR Tambo..? https://t.co/sVWlxVVqxO&mdash; LillyBee (@LynnDipB) March 8, 2017Apparently R24 Million heist is nothing, R100 Million heist is the biggest heist ever made in SA in the same Airport, OR Tambo.?? pic.twitter.com/vDJfHJfltO&mdash; Mondly Shezi (@_Mondly) March 8, 2017Soooo about R24m was stolen from this SAA PLANE that they robbed at OR Tambo last night....lol something about this story doesn't add up pic.twitter.com/FVGb912VyI&mdash; Maximus (